  refactoring,L2,Refactoring Necessity Assessment,true,"Code quality analysis of 3 modified files (coordinator.md: 38 lines, worker.md: 57 lines, defs-stage4.ts: 196 lines) shows clean structure, proper separation of concerns, template reuse via ${REFACTORING_STRATEGY}, and compliance with 200-line constraint. No code duplication detected. Single responsibility principle consistently applied.\n\n**Refactoring verdict: NOT REQUIRED**\n\nHowever, **blocking issue identified:**\n- Prerequisite sections from state_machine phase (commit 25db124) are present in git history but DELETED in current working directory\n- \"Phase Output Rules\" (11 lines) removed from coordinator.md\n- \"Edit Completeness Rules\" missing from worker.md\n- Test failures (7/12) directly attributable to missing sections, not code quality issues\n- This is a state_machine DoD issue, not refactoring scope\n\nGit diff confirms deletion: `-## Phase Output Rules` and related content marked for removal.\n\n**Recommendation:** Phase advancement requires restoration of deleted sections and re-test. Current code structure is sound—no refactoring needed.","2026-03-29T10:55:58.517Z"
